## SLIDE 7 — Feature 4: Deep-Dive Investigation Mode
**[Show: [server.py](file:///c:/Users/musta/OneDrive/Desktop/new_etl/summarizer/server.py) — the `/investigate` endpoint + the UI 'Launch Deep-Dive' button]**

> "Standard briefings are great, but sometimes you want to go deeper. OmniNews includes an **Autonomous Deep-Dive** mode.
>
> When a user clicks 'Launch Deep-Dive' on any briefing, it triggers the same agent pipeline — but in **high-autonomy mode**. The `is_deep_dive` flag is set to `True`, which tells the router to allow up to **5 research turns** instead of 1. The Researcher's persona also changes — from a news researcher to a 'Private Investigator' that gathers hidden details, primary sources, and conflicting reports.
>
> Technically, this is triggered via a **FastAPI POST endpoint** (`/investigate/{cluster_id}`) that runs in a background thread. The result is saved directly to the `investigative_report` column in the database, and the frontend picks it up instantly via **Supabase Realtime** WebSocket subscriptions — no page refresh needed."

---

## SLIDE 8 — Feature 5: Narrative Duel — Dialectical AI Debate
**[Show: [duel_graph.py](file:///c:/Users/musta/OneDrive/Desktop/new_etl/summarizer/agents/duel_graph.py) + the Narrative Duel UI component]**

> "This is the most unique feature of OmniNews: the **Narrative Duel**. It uses a completely separate LangGraph called the [DuelState](file:///c:/Users/musta/OneDrive/Desktop/new_etl/summarizer/agents/duel_graph.py#12-22) graph.
>
> For any briefing, the user can trigger a side-by-side AI debate between two opposing geopolitical personas:
>
> - **The Atlanticist Analyst** — Represents the Western security establishment. Its system prompt tells it to analyze from the perspective of NATO, the G7, and global market stability. It focuses on supply chain security, democratic alliances, and the liberal international order.
> - **The Global South Realist** — Represents regional sovereignty. Its system prompt tells it to analyze from the perspective of BRICS+, non-Western alliances, and anti-hegemonic interests. It highlights the impact of Western intervention and sanctions on developing nations.
>
> Both agents receive the **exact same headline and context** — including the full investigative report if one exists — but their prompts force them to interpret it through radically different lenses.
>
> After both agents produce their reports, the graph moves to a **Synthesizer Node** — a 'Dialectical Intelligence Node' that:
> 1. Identifies **Points of Convergence** — facts or risks both perspectives agree on
> 2. Identifies **Points of Divergence** — where their core interpretations conflict
> 3. Outputs a structured JSON with `convergence`, `divergence`, `west_summary`, and `south_summary`
>
> The graph is wired as a strict linear pipeline: `Atlanticist → Global South → Synthesizer → END`. This gives the user a **360-degree view** of any global event — something no single news source can provide."


